---
import ContentPage from '../layouts/ContentPage.astro';
import { languageAlternates } from '../lib/i18n';

const description =
  'A company LLM stack you actually control: models, your data, who can ask what, what it costs, and who gets paged when it breaks.';

const alternates = languageAlternates('/corporate-llm/', '/de/corporate-llm/');

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'WebPage',
      '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/#webpage',
      url: 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/',
      name: 'Corporate LLM',
      description,
      inLanguage: 'en',
      isPartOf: { '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/#website' },
      author: { '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/#person' },
      about: {
        '@type': 'DefinedTerm',
        name: 'Corporate LLM',
        description,
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Service',
      '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/#service',
      name: 'Corporate LLM',
      url: 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/',
      description,
      provider: { '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/#person' },
      areaServed: ['DE', 'EU', 'Worldwide'],
      serviceType: 'Corporate LLM platform build',
    },
  ],
};
---

<ContentPage
  title="Corporate LLM - Lars Ullrich"
  description={description}
  canonical="/corporate-llm/"
  noteId="corporate-llm"
  heading="Corporate LLM"
  eyebrow="Platform"
  lead="Skip the chatbot bolted onto Slack. Build a stack that runs under your rules."
  icon="/graphics/icon-model-orbits.svg"
  alternates={alternates}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  localeSwitch={{ href: '/de/corporate-llm/', label: 'Deutsch' }}
>
  <p>
    That's what I mean by Corporate LLM. Where the data lives. Who can ask what. What the model is allowed to touch. What it costs per week. Who owns the pager. Typical project runs about six to twelve weeks, depending on how tangled the starting point is.
  </p>

  <h2>What we put in place</h2>
  <p>
    We pick models that fit: hosted APIs when they're fine, open weights you host when data, cost, or lock-in say otherwise. RAG and tools over the docs and systems you approve, with clear edges. Access control, audit trails, budget or rate limits. Monitoring and evals so you can keep it alive after launch.
  </p>

  <h2>Versus a Build Sprint</h2>
  <p>
    A Build Sprint ships one product with AI inside it. Corporate LLM is the shared layer lots of teams (sometimes customers) use under company policy. Same bar for engineering. Wider scope.
  </p>

  <h2>Where to start</h2>
  <p>
    Still arguing platform versus one use case?
    <a href="/services/readiness-audit/">Do the audit first</a>.
    Already sure you need a private or hybrid stack? This engagement is the one.
  </p>
</ContentPage>
